    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-06-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-06-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="211"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d211">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Mason</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Uhl</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">United States Consulate General</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Frankfort</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-06-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 22, 1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 314.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to your instructions No. 153 of May 3,
                    and my report of May 22 in response thereto, I have now to transmit herewith an
                    officially sealed sample of evaporated apples taken from a lot which was
                    imported by Mi. Erwin Roelker, of Frankfort, from Albert Petri, of Rochester, N.
                    Y., and which have been condemned by the police and health authorities of
                    Frankfort as containing, per kilogram, from 0.0035 to 0.0515 gram of zinc or
                    salts of zinc, a proportion which is adjudged prejudicial to human health.</p>
                <p>This sample bears the Real and certificate of the police court before which the
                    proceedings against Mr. J. Latscha, the retailer of the apples took place.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Frank H. Mason</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Consul-General.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
